.Dd September 21, 2002
.Dt PREEMPT 9
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm preempt
.Nd general preempt function
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Fd #include \*[Lt]sys/proc.h\*[Gt]
.Fd #include \*[Lt]sys/sched.h\*[Gt]
.Ft void
.Fn preempt "struct proc *p"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn preempt
function puts the current process back on the system run queue
and performs an involuntary context switch.  If the specified process
arguement
.Fa p
is not NULL then a context switch is done to that process.  Otherwise,
the normal process selection criteria inside
.Xr mi_switch 9
is used to select the new process.
.Pp
The
.Fn preempt
function must not be called with the scheduler lock held.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr setrunqueue 9 ,
.Xr mi_switch 9 ,
.Xr userret 9
